-- K+S Names Radmacher to Executive Board to Head Potash Division
-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 2013-03-26T09:11:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-26/k-s-names-radmacher-to-executive-board-to-head-potash-division.html
K+S AG (SDF) , Europe’s largest potash
maker, named Andreas Radmacher to its executive board to oversee
the company’s potash and magnesium operations.  Radmacher, 47, will join the board on Sept. 1, Kassel,
Germany-based K+S said today in an e-mailed statement. Radmacher
is head of  RWE AG (RWE) ’s Turkish unit in Istanbul and was previously
a member of the executive board of RWE Energy AG in Dortmund,
 Germany .  With Radmacher’s appointment, half of K+S’s management
board will have been in their jobs for 15 months or less. The
board will expand to six members again after Joachim Felker
retired in September. Chief Executive Officer Norbert Steiner
had temporarily taken responsibility for the potash and
magnesium business unit, K+S said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
